WEBVTT

00:02.613 --> 00:05.748
Mmm, another great dinner, Ma.

00:05.749 --> 00:06.782
Thanks, Mikey.

00:06.783 --> 00:08.217
Makes me feel good
to know you get

00:08.218 --> 00:10.585
at least one decent meal a week.

00:10.587 --> 00:12.721
Well, you know I cook for him.

00:12.723 --> 00:13.788
I know.

00:14.725 --> 00:16.459
Peggy, healthy food
can be delicious, too.

00:16.460 --> 00:17.492
Right, Mike?

00:17.494 --> 00:20.061
Yeah, that's what you keep
telling me.

00:21.398 --> 00:22.598
Hey, by the way,
what are you doing

00:22.599 --> 00:24.799
next Wednesday at 5:30 a.m.?

00:24.801 --> 00:25.968
Um, let's see.

00:25.969 --> 00:28.203
Unless I get a paper route
I will be sleeping.

00:28.205 --> 00:29.537
Mm.

00:29.539 --> 00:33.075
My church group is taking a van
to the casino in Rockford.

00:33.076 --> 00:34.577
I could use a seatmate

00:34.578 --> 00:37.178
and maybe we could go halfsies
on a penny slot.

00:37.180 --> 00:38.681
Wait a minute,
is this next Wednesday?

00:38.682 --> 00:41.484
I actually have a real excuse
why I can't go.

00:41.485 --> 00:44.986
I got tickets for that pl...
I got tickets for a play.

00:44.988 --> 00:47.222
Oh, yeah, you're going to see
that thing about werewolves.

00:47.224 --> 00:50.793
I'm, well, I'm going to see
a play at Steppenwolf.

00:50.794 --> 00:54.262
It's the most, it's the most
famous theater in Chicago?

00:54.264 --> 00:58.333
Right, and thank you
for not making me go.

00:58.335 --> 01:00.902
All right, I'll go
to your werewolf play,

01:00.904 --> 01:02.538
but next time we do my thing.

01:02.539 --> 01:03.872
Wait, what?
If you're going to take a trip

01:03.874 --> 01:06.274
with my ma, can I have
the guys over for cards?

01:06.276 --> 01:08.143
No, we're not taking
a trip together.

01:08.145 --> 01:10.712
So, I go to your dumb play
and you do squat for me?

01:10.714 --> 01:12.914
I never asked you to come
to the play with me.

01:12.916 --> 01:15.350
Oh, fine, after I rearranged
my whole schedule.

01:15.352 --> 01:16.918
You didn't change anything.

01:16.920 --> 01:19.088
So, is that a no on poker?
Yes.

01:19.089 --> 01:21.190
So that's a yes on poker? No.

01:21.191 --> 01:22.157
All right.

01:22.159 --> 01:23.125
Don't snap at him.

01:23.126 --> 01:24.894
You're the one
promising him things

01:24.895 --> 01:26.027
and then taking them away.

01:26.029 --> 01:28.296
All right, we're done.
Dinner's over.

01:28.298 --> 01:30.298
Oh, fine, go ahead and go.

01:30.300 --> 01:33.234
Cut into the only time I spend
with my son all week.

01:33.236 --> 01:34.370
There it is.

01:34.371 --> 01:36.038
Okay, if you're not
being a bully,

01:36.039 --> 01:37.173
you're playing the martyr.

01:37.174 --> 01:38.974
You know why I don't want
to take a trip with you?

01:38.975 --> 01:41.910
Because you are 100%
pure uncut misery.

01:41.912 --> 01:44.312
You suck the joy out
of any situation.

01:44.314 --> 01:47.782
You are a joyless
fun-sucker. Yeah.

01:47.784 --> 01:50.018
All right.

01:50.020 --> 01:51.253
Let me have it, Peggy.

01:51.254 --> 01:53.823
Okay, vomit up the bile
like you always do.

01:53.824 --> 01:57.659
Tell me why I'm such a horrible,
ungrateful daughter-in-law.

01:59.596 --> 02:01.697
Mom?

02:01.698 --> 02:02.897
Oh, faking

02:02.899 --> 02:03.899
a heart attack.

02:03.900 --> 02:05.934
Classic fun-sucker move.

02:05.936 --> 02:07.469
Molly, she's not faking.

02:07.471 --> 02:08.904
Call 911.

02:08.905 --> 02:10.573
Oh, my God.

02:10.574 --> 02:12.808
Okay. All right.

02:12.809 --> 02:14.710
Oh, I can't...
I hate this purse.

02:14.711 --> 02:15.945
I can't find anything.

02:15.946 --> 02:16.912
Use the landline.

02:16.913 --> 02:18.380
Good idea. Good idea.

02:18.381 --> 02:19.547
It's okay, Ma. It's okay.

02:19.549 --> 02:20.549
Keep listening to my voice.

02:20.550 --> 02:21.750
You're gonna be okay.

02:21.752 --> 02:23.252
Okay, I dialed my cell phone.

02:23.253 --> 02:25.720
When it rings, pick it up
and then dial 911.

02:25.722 --> 02:27.623
Just call 911!

02:27.624 --> 02:28.357
Better.

02:28.358 --> 02:31.059
You're going to be okay.

02:31.695 --> 02:34.530
